Commentary: OUT! Bowled! 5-fer to finish a tremendous last over. His 4th 5-wicket haul in ODIs. Around off, Shami moves across to paddle but misses the ball hits his pads and goes onto hit the stumps. 2 wickets and just 3 runs from the final over. Top notch from Mustafizur. INDIA FINISH WITH 314/9 FROM THEIR 50 OVERS.

WIDE AND RUN OUT! Slower delivery outside off, it is on the wrong side of the tramline. Shami comes for a run. Bhuvi was slow though. Rahim throws it to Mustafizur, who hits the stumps at the bowler's end. The umpire takes it upstairs but Bhuvneshwar had started to walk back even before the replays rolled in.
Back of a length ball on off, Shami pulls it to deep mid-wicket and gets a single.
Just 1 run off the 4 balls. This is World Class stuff. Good length ball on off, Kumar punches it to the side of the pitch and gets a single.

OUT! No Dhoni magic in the last over. Slower bouncer away from the body, Dhoni looks to flat-bat it straight over the bowler's head. It comes off the upper half of his bat and goes to the left of mid on. Shakib moves across to his left hand side and takes an easy catch.
Another dot. Bangladesh will take this. Short and slow, Dhoni pulls it to Shakib at short mid-wicket.
Good length ball on off, Dhoni flat-bats it towards long off but refuses to take a single.
Good length ball on off, Dhoni comes down the track and pushes it towards cover to get a single.
FOUR! Dhoni rolling back the years and silencing his critics here. Slower delivery around off, Dhoni cuts it and pierces the gap through point for a boundary.
Slower delivery outside off, Dhoni swings his bat at this but misses.
Fuller on off, Dhoni drives it but finds mid off.
FOUR! Driven with brutality! Length ball around off, Dhoni uses his bottom hand and drives it with power through covers for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, Dhoni strokes it wide of sweeper cover and gets two.
Slower bouncer to end the over. Bhuvneshwar ducks under it. End of a fabulous over. Just 3 runs and a wicket off it.
Length delivery around off, Dhoni runs it down to third man and gets to the other end. 300 comes up for India with that.
Good length ball outside off, Dhoni lets it carry to the keeper.
Good length ball on off, Bhuvneshwar pushes it towards cover and gets a single. Bhuvi is off the mark.

OUT! Caught! Karthik does not leave a lasting impression in his first outing. Mustafizur bends his back on this one and bowls a slower bouncer. Karthik looks to pull but the ball rises onto him. He ends up getting a top edge which goes to the left of cover. Mosaddek there moves on that side and takes a simple catch.
On the pads, Dhoni flicks it towards mid-wicket and gets a single.

Almost a calamity there. Fuller around off, Dhoni strokes it towards third man and takes a single. Karthik wanted a second as the ball went past the keeper. Dhoni though rightfully sends him back. 9 runs off the over.
Now comes down the track and flicks it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Creamed! Full around off, Karthik creams it away through point and gets a boundary.
Full on off, Dhoni pushes it towards cover and gets to the other end.
Good length ball on off, DK punches it to sweeper cover for a single.
Length ball on off, Dhoni strokes it towards point and gets a single.
Fuller on off, Karthik pushes it to the man at cover.
Back of a length ball around off, Dhoni pulls it to square leg and rotates the strike.
Cut nicely but there is a man at third man for a single.
On the pads, Dhoni flicks it to the on side and gets a single.

Good length ball on off, Dhoni punches it towards cover and takes a single. The fielder there scores a direct hit at the bowler's end but Dhoni was in. The ball then deflects off the stumps towards mid-wicket allowing them to take one more. Two taken.
FOUR! Punched and punched with power. Good length ball around off, Dhoni gets on his back foot and punches it hard through point for a boundary.
On middle, Karthik looks to flick but gets a leading edge which goes back towards the bowler. Excellent sell from Shakib. 10-0-41-1 here.
Beautiful. Away spinner pitching on off, Dinesh looks to defend but misses.
On middle and leg, Dhoni flicks it to the on side and gets a single.
Floated on off, Dhoni defends it off the front foot.
On the pads, DK gets off the mark in this World Cup with a simple flick.

OUT! Pant holes out! Fumble but taken. The risk of giving Shakib the ball against Pant has worked. He bowls it slower through the air on off and middle, Pant goes for a big slog sweep. He does not time it and it goes straight to Mosaddek at deep backward square leg. He fumbles the first time, the ball hits his shoulder and then comes back down. He fumbles for the second time as well but manages to hold onto it on the third time.
FOUR! Pulled and pulled fine. Short ball on middle, Dhoni pulls it over square leg for a boundary. Good end to the over this.
On middle and leg, Dhoni flicks it but finds short mid-wicket.
On off, Pant guides it down to third man and gets a single.
Another play and miss. Outside off on a length, Pant looks to drive again but misses.
Good length ball outside off, Pant looks to drive but misses.

FOUR LEG BYES! Slower one to begin the over. It is down the leg side, Pant looks to flick but it goes off his thigh pad. The ball bounces in front of Mushfiqur and he misfields. The ball goes past him to the third man fence.
Short on off, Dhoni punches it to cover.
Floated on off, Dhoni pushes it to cover.
This time glances it wide of short mid-wicket and gets a single.
On the pads, Pant flicks it to the man at mid-wicket.
Short around off, Pant cuts it wide of sweeper cover. Rubel Hossain in the deep runs and dives to his left. He fumbles so they get the second with ease.
On the pads, Pant glances it to the man at short fine leg.
Short ball on off, Pant pulls it to fine leg and keeps the strike.
Good length ball on the pads, Dhoni flicks it wide of mid-wicket and gets three as it is hit on the longer side of the boundary.
Length ball on off, Dhoni punches it to the man at cover.
On the pads, Pant turns it behind square on the leg side and gets a single.
Back of a length ball on off, Pant pulls it to short mid-wicket. Pant wanted a run but Dhoni says no.
WIDE! Bounce bounces too high. It is over the head of Pant and it has been wided.
FOUR! Poor start to the over for Mustafizur. He drags it down on the body, Pant pulls it over square leg and gets a boundary.
Short on off, Dhoni punches it back to the bowler.
Shorter on off, Pant cuts it to deep point and gets to the other end.
On the middle and leg, Pant turns it to mid-wicket.
Drag down this one. But it keeps low, MS punches it to long on and gets a single.
Short again on off, Pant this time cuts it towards point and takes one.
Short on off, Dhoni punches it to long off and gets a single.
Good length ball on off, Dhoni punches it to sweeper cover and gets a single.
Once again pulls it but this time there is a man in the deep at mid-wicket so just a single.

FOUR! Hat-trick of boundaries here for Pant. Pressure on the bowler now. Good length ball around off, Pant shows his quick hand work and cuts it through point for a boundary. This is the best shot of the lot.
FOUR! Two in two for Pant! Short ball around the body, Pant picks the length early and whacks his pull over mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR! Crisply driven. Fuller outside off, Pant gets on his front foot and drives it nonchalantly through covers for a boundary.
Back of a length ball, Pant defends it off the back foot.
Good length ball on off, Dhoni punches it to cover. End of an excellent over. It is a double-wicket maiden from Mustafizur.
Outside off, Dhoni calmly leaves it alone.

OUT! Pandya goes for a duck! Second wicket in the over for Mustafizur and this is the second big fish off just 3 balls. Mashrafe keeps a wide first slip for Pandya. Mustafizur rolls his fingers on this one and bowls it outside off. Hardik Pandya shuffles across and looks to punch it. He ends up getting a thick outside edge, which goes to the right of Sarkar at wide first slip who takes a very fine low catch. No Pandya show today. This is a big blow for India. The onus to up the run rate has been on Hardik in the tournament.
Hardik starts his innings with a careful front foot defense.

OUT! Kohli holes out! Another wicket which has come against the run of play here. The bowling change has worked here for Bangladesh and Mashrafe. Mustafizur bends his back and bowls it short. Kohli goes for a big pull, he times it well but does not get the desired elevation. The ball goes to the man at deep mid-wicket. Rubel Hossain stationed there stretches his hands up in the air and takes a fine catch. The skipper's streak of 5 consecutive 50-plus scores comes to an end.
Good length ball on off, Kohli punches it to the man at cover.
Good running this! Good length ball on middle and leg, Pant flicks it wide of deep mid-wicket. Kohli wants two and he has young Pant with him so he gets it with ease.
The keeper comes up now. It is on the pads, Pant looks to flick but it goes off his pads.
Fuller on off, Kohli drives it to the left of mid off and gets a single.
Full on middle, Kohli whips it with great timing wide of deep mid-wicket and they get a couple.
On the pads, Pant now plays a proper flick and gets a single.
FOUR! WOW! Pant showing his innovative strokes here. He premeditates his sweep. Soumya bowls it on the body but Pant still goes with it and gets it past short fine leg for a boundary.
On the pads, Pant turns it to square leg and gets a single.
Now tries to show aggression and comes down the track. He yorks himself around off, but Pant gets his bat down in time.
FOUR! This is smart from young Pant. Shakib tosses it on the pads, Pant sees there is no one in the deep at square leg so he just plays a good looking sweep there and fetches himself a boundary.
Tossed up on off, Kohli nudges it to long off and gets to the other end.
Now calmly defends the next ball towards point.
FOUR! What a shot! This shows the class of Kohli. Floated on middle, Kohli comes down the track and whips it away through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Back of a length ball on off, Kohli defends it with soft hands and takes a single.
Short ball, Kohli pulls it to short mid-wicket.

On the pads, Kohli flicks it behind square and gets a couple. Wait a minute, Mashrafe is asking for a review but the DRS time is up. Also, it has been given as a run. So what was he thinking? Soumya thinks it has hit his boot first. Replays show that it came right off the middle of Virat's bat.
Slower ball on the pads, Pant flicks it to the on side and gets to the other end.
On off and middle, Kohli drives it to long on and rotates the strike.
Good length ball on off, Pant lofts it over covers but gets just a single.
Slower one on top of off, Pant guides it down to third man and keeps the strike with a comfortable single.
Around off, Pant defends it to point.
Good running. Length ball on off, Kohli taps it towards point and calls for a quick single. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses.
Better ball this. Good length ball on off, Kohli defends it with authority.
FOUR! Whipped as smooth as butter! Full around off, Kohli flicks it through mid-wicket. Mortaza at short mid-wicket does not even move an inch as the ball goes past him like a rocket.
Too straight on the pads, Pant looks to flick but misses. The ball goes off his thigh pad towards fine leg and they take a leg bye.
Now smartly flicks this one and gets a simple single.
SIX! That has disappeared way into the stands. Floated on middle and off, Pant comes down the track and demolishes it over the long on fence for a huge six. First boundary for Pant.
Tossed up on middle and off, Pant blocks it off his front foot.
Shorter on the pads, Pant looks to flick but misses. Mosaddek and Rahim go up in appeal but the umpire turns it down.
Tossed up on the stumps, Pant defends it off the front foot.
Floated on off, Pant comes down the track and defends it.
WIDE! Bowls it down the leg side, Pant looks to flick but misses. Wide signalled.
Pant is off the mark. Good length ball on the pads, Pant flicks it to square leg and keeps the strike with a single.
Nervous start from Pant. He started it this way in the last game too. Good length ball outside off, Pant has a poke at it but misses.

OUT! Rahul departs! Slower delivery outside off, Rahul looks to cut but gets a thick outside edge which goes to Mushfiqur behind the stumps. He dives to his right and takes a very good low catch. Once again Rahul gets a start in this World Cup but cannot convert it. Two wickets in relatively quick succession for Bangladesh and now they are into India's rusty middle order.
Follows it up with a single down to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Exquisite! Overpitched on off, Kohli gets on his front foot and drives it handsomely straight as an arrow for a beautiful boundary.
Play and a miss. It is on the fourth stump line. A line which tempts the batsman to drive. Kohli too  goes for it but misses.
On top of the stumps, Kohli punches it wide of mid off and keeps the strike.
Good length ball on middle, Kohli turns it behind square on the leg side and gets a couple.
Slower ball which is almost as full as a yorker. Kohli strokes it to mid on.
Length ball on off, Kohli taps it back to the bowler.
On the pads, Rahul flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Good length ball on off, Rahul comes down the track and lofts it over point. The sweeper cover runs to his left and parries it to Rubel Hossain who comes from third man. Two taken.
Length delivery on off, Rahul punches it to the man at cover.
Fuller on off, KL strokes it to the off side and gets to the other end.
Kohli is off the mark! Fuller on off, Kohli defends it with soft hands towards cover and gets off the mark after 4 dot balls.
On the pads, Kohli plays a strong flick shot but it is to the man at short mid-wicket.
Outside off, Rahul cuts it to deep point and gets a single.
On the stumps, Rahul defends it off the front foot.
Fuller on middle and leg, Kohli looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
On the stumps, Kohli defends it calmly.
Kohli starts his innings with a solid front foot defense.
On the pads, Rahul flicks it to square leg and gets to the other end.

OUT! Caught! This has come against the run of play. End of a terrific knock this. Knowing Rohit though he will be gutted. Sarkar bowls it full around off, Rohit looks to hit it over mid off. He does not time it well though as the bat turns in his hand. It goes to the left of mid off. Liton Das at mid off moves to that side and takes an easy catch. End of a fabulous innings by Rohit. He walks off to a well deserved ovation form the crowd.
FOUR! Poor ball this. On the pads, Rohit won't miss out on that especially at this stage of his innings. He flicks it with ease through mid-wicket for a boundary.

100 FOR ROHIT! His 4th in this World Cup. What a player! What a knock this has been! The Hit Man gets to his 26th ODI hundred with a cut to deep point. He raises the bat in appreciation and soaks in all the applause.
Makes the crowd wait as he taps it back to the bowler.
Rahul flicks it to the on side and gives the strike to Rohit.
Comes down the track and milks it to long on for another run. Moves to 99.
Ohh! That one stays low. Straighter one outside off, Rohit looks to cut but the ball keeps low. It misses the stumps and hits the pad of the keeper.
Floated on off, Rohit strokes it to cover. He looks for a single but then does not go with it. Good call, the single was never there.
Good length ball on off, Rahul strokes it to mid on. Another over ends without troubling the two batsmen.
Outside off, Rohit cuts it to deep point and rotates the strike.
On off, Rohit punches it to cover.
WIDE! Bouncer bounces too high. It goes over the head of Rohit. It has been wided.
On the fourth stump line, Rahul slaps it hard but there is a man at sweeper cover so just one.
Good length ball around off, Rahul makes room and punches it straight back to the bowler.
Fuller on off, Rohit slaps it to sweeper cover and rotates the strike.
On the stumps, Rahul blocks it.
Shorter on off, Rohit punches it towards mid-wicket and gets a single. Moves to 96.
On middle, Rahul flicks it to mid-wicket for one more.
Shorter on middle, Rohit tucks it towards mid-wicket and looks for two. The fielder from mid on gets to the ball quickly so he has to be happy with single.
Floated on off, Rahul nudges it to cover and gets to the other end.
Spinning away from around off, Rohit eases it towards cover and gets to the other end.
Short ball around the body, Rahul looks to pull but misses. Mushfiqur goes up in appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Review not taken by Mashrafe.
On the pads, Rahul shuffles across and strokes it to mid-wicket.
Good length delivery on middle, Rohit nudges it to the right of mid on and takes an easy run.
Good length ball on off, Rohit easily pushes it to cover.
Slightly fuller on middle, KL strokes it to long on and takes a single.
Starts with a length ball on off, KL punches it to cover.
The batsman has punched the ball off the back foot. They pick up a single.
Nicely played! This is outside off, Rahul plays it late, he guides it past point for two.
Good length and on off, this is whipped to mid on.
Extra bounce! Well played in the end! Shorter and on off, it takes off after pitching. Rahul does well to take one hand off the handle and defend it.
That has been crunched but just for one. Full and outside off, this is hit through covers for one.
Good length and on off, this is defended.
Outside off, Sharma opens the face of the bat and guides it down to third man for one.
Hit fine for two! This is shorter and on the body, Sharma pulls it towards fine leg for two.
Good length and on off, it is kept out.
Soft leading edge! This is angled into the batter, Rahul looks to work it on the leg side but closes the face of the bat, it goes off the leading edge to point for a run.
Goes back to bowling length on the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.

SIX! Beautiful, delightful! Probably the best shot of the game. 300th six of the World Cup. This is full and on off, Rohit extends his arms and just lofts it nonchalantly over the bowler's head for a biggie. Also, the 150 is up.
A quick run to end another good over for India. Shorter on middle, Sharma works it to mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
This is on the pads, rahul guides it down to third man for one.
Back of a length on off, Rahul pushes it back to the bowler.
Clever batting! Follows the boundary up with a single down to third man for one.

FOUR! No one there and another boundary! Not timed perfectly but Rohit gets the desired result. This is short and hurries onto the batsman. Rohit looks to pull it over mid-wicket but since he is a touch late in the shot, it goes over mid on for a boundary.
Good length and on middle, this is worked towards fine leg for one.

FOUR! Rohit seems to have stepped on the gas here. A six earlier in the over and now a four. He steps down the track, makes it into a full toss and lofts it over the mid-wicket fielder for a boundary. 13 from the over.
A yorker on middle, Rohit jams it back to the bowler.
The batsman has driven it through mid on. One run added to the total.
Flatter and on middle, Rohit pushes it down to long on for one.
SIX! That is colossal! Right off the middle. Also, the risk was minimum as Rohit hit it with the turn. This is floated up on off, Rohit lofts it high and handsome over the long on fence.
Rahul makes room but Hossain slows it up and lands it on the stumps. Rahul gently pushes it through covers for one.
Good running! This is on a length and around off, Rahul drops it towards point. He wants a run but Rohit hesitates, in the end they go for it and make it.
This is around off, Rohit guides it towards backward point for one.
On the fuller side, Rohit pushes it to mid off.

In the air but no one there! Short and outside off, Rohit looks to drag his pull over mid-wicket. The ball takes the top edge, clears the mid-wicket fielder who runs back and manages to push the ball back in. Two taken.
Good length and on off, Rohit guides it to point.
Loose stroke! This is outside off and on a length. Rohit hangs his bat out but gets beaten.
Leading edge but short! On middle, Rahul looks to work it on the leg side but closes the face of the bat early, he gets a leading edge which lands short of the bowler.
Very full and on the leg stump, Rohit swings but it goes off the inner half through square leg for one. 500 runs for Rohit in this World Cup. Only the second Indian to do so after Sachin Tendulkar.
Floats it up on off, Rahul comes down the track and also makes room and hits it through covers for one.
On the stumps, this is hit down to long on for one.
Another single as Rahul works it through mid-wicket with the turn.
Shorter and down the leg side, Rohit pulls it to deep backward square leg for one.
FOUR! A boundary to start the over and one to end! Another top-class shot. Fuller and on off, Rahul leans into it and times it through covers. No stopping those. An expensive start by Rubel.
Risky shot! This is on the pads, Sharma works it through mid-wicket for one. He hit that right off the stumps, he needed to get bat on ball there.
This is on the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
BEATEN! This is on a length and around off, this pitches and shapes away. Rahul looks to drive but is beaten by the away movement.

Misfield sees Rahul go to his half ton! Both the openers get a half ton now. Rahul though would be very eager to make this count. He hasn't got a big score yet. This is on the pads, it is worked towards mid-wicket where the fielder lets it through. Two taken.
FOUR! Straight as an arrow! Another bowler is greeted into the attack by a boundary. A half volley on off, Rohit hits it through mid on and the ball races away to the fence.
The batter uses his feet and strokes it down to long on for one.
On the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Another sweep shot, this time it is by Rahul and straight towards deep square leg for one.
On the stumps, Rohit pushes it back to the bowler again.
Down the leg side, Rohit sweeps it through backward square leg for a brace.
This is flatter and on middle, Rohit pushes it back to the bowler.
On the bounce! This is floated up on off, Rohit looks to sweep but it goes off the top edge, well short of the deep mid-wicket fielder for one.
On off, this is blocked.
Floats it up on off, Rahul strokes it through covers for one.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Excellent stop! Shorter and outside off, Rahul plays it late, he cuts it towards point where the fielder dives to his left and saves a boundary.
An appeal but not sure why? This is outside off, Rahul shuffles right across and looks to sweep but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
A dot to end! So back-to-back good overs for India. Bangladesh fail to continue the little pressure that was building. Fuller and on off, this is hit to covers.
Three now! Rahul backs away, looking to hit it on the off side. Mash follows him. Rahul adjusts and works it through wide mid on and takes three.
SIX! That has been powered! Slightly shorter and around off, Rahul goes back and pulls it away over the wide long on fence. Second six in the last two overs.
Good length again and on off, Rahul pushes it to covers.
On the off pole, the batter defends it out.
This is on the pads, it is worked towards backward square leg for one.
Floated up on off, this is hit through covers for one. An expensive over by Shakib. 9 from it.
Flatter and outside off, Rahul now pushes it through covers for one.
Fifty for Rohit Sharma. His excellent World Cup continues and he has a chance to score another big century here. He gets there by slapping this through covers for one.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
SIX! Shorter boundary but it would not have mattered! This is short and on middle, Rohit has enough time to go back and pull it high and handsome over the mid-wicket fence.
Well bowled again! This is slower and it lands on off, it pitches and turns away again. Rohit does well to bail out of his shot after looking at the turn.
Another dot! Back of a length on off, this is pushed to covers.

This lands around off, it pitches and comes back in a little. Rohit guides it late towards point and gets to the other end. Mash has started to get his lines right here. He is attacking the stumps and also bowling it away from the hitting zone of the batter.
Another back of a length delivery, Rohit pushes it through covers, it is away from the sweeper for two.
Back of a length on off, Rahul pushes it through covers and gets to the other end.
This is on the pads, Rahul looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
This is on middle, Rahul works it to mid-wicket.
This is flatter and on middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Played to the point region by the batsman.
Risky shot! This is angled into the off pole, Rohit goes back and tries to cut but it goes off the outside edge to backward point.
Another tossed up ball on off, Rohit blocks it out.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed down to long off for one.
Floated up on off, this is hit to covers.
This is on the pads, it is worked through mid-wicket for one. A better over from Mash, just the two from it.
Fuller and on off, Rahul strokes it to mid off. Just the single from the over.
Back of a length again and on off, Rahul pushes it to mid off.
On the stumps, this is pushed back to the bowler.
Well bowled! Goes wide of the crease and bowls it on off, this one skids through. Rahul gets his bat in time and keeps it out.
Fuller and on off, this is driven through covers for one.
Flighted on off, Rahul strokes it to covers. A very good over by Shakib. He got the ball to turn and bounce. Bangladesh will already be regretting why they did not take another spinner.
WIDE! Down the leg side and it has been wided.
Punched off the back foot by the batsman. The batsmen have run through for a single.
Another loopy ball on off, Sharma strokes it to covers.
BEATEN! Extra bounce now! Slower and just outside off, Rohit looks to throw his bat at it but is beaten by the extra bounce.
Slightly shorter this time and it is flatter outside off, Rohit cuts it but finds point.
Slight turn there! Good delivery to begin! This floated up on off, it pitches and straightens. Rohit looks to defend but ends up playing inside the line.
A crisp drive! Fuller and on off, Rahul drives it to the man at covers. A dot to end the 10th. India's Powerplay 1 by a big margin, they are 69 for 0.
Bowls it on the leg side now, Rohit works it through square leg and takes one. Sensible batting.

FOUR! Room on offer with third man up, it is not a good idea. Short and outside off, Rohit waits for the ball to come to him and then guides it past backward point for a boundary. Easy pickings for Rohit.
This is on middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket for one.
Good length and on off, it is kept out.

FOUR! Welcome back in the attack, Mashrafe. Another cracking shot. Rahul takes a few steps ahead, he still does not get to the pitch of the ball. Rahul strokes it on the up through mid off for a boundary.

Well bowled and nicely played! On a good length around off, this straightens after pitching. Rahul opens the face of the bat and guides it down to third man for one. Another productive over for India.
A single now! Shorter and on middle, Rohit hops and works it towards square leg for one.
Another delivery angled into the batter, Rohit works it towards mid-wicket.
Goes around the wicket and cramps the batsman for room by bowling it closer to the body, Rohit works it towards mid-wicket.

FOUR! Makes full use of the Free Hit! It is a freebie actually. It is full and outside off, Rohit just carves it over the in-field and then it races to the point boundary. Once again consecutive boundaries for India. They are off to a flier here.

FOUR! Lovely, just lovely! It is raining boundaries here. This is full and around off, going away with the angle. Rohit just puts bat to ball, guides it through the left of mid off and the ball races to the fence. Also, the bowler has overstepped so it is a no ball. Free Hit coming up. 50 up for India, that too in quick time.
Fuller and on middle, once again it is on the straighter side, this is flicked through mid-wicket for one.
A single to end another good over for India. Full and on the pads, this is flicked through square leg for one.
Could have easily been three in a row! This is short and on middle, Rahul is into the pull shot a touch early, it goes off the bottom edge towards the leg side.
FOUR! This shot had class written all over it. This is slightly fuller around off, Rahul leans into it and caresses it through extra cover. Back-to-back boundaries.
FOUR! Poor ball and put away! This is down the leg side, Rahul just needed to get bat on ball, he does so and it races to the fine leg fence.
This time he bowls it outside off, Rohit guides it down to third man and gets to the other end.
A little too straight, Rahul works it through mid-wicket and takes a run.
Lands it on a length close to off, Rohit turns his wrists slightly and pushes it to mid on. 6 from this over, it's been a good positive start from India.
The line is too straight, KL eases it to the left of the mid-wicket fielder and pinches a run.
Presses forward to a full ball and presents the full face of his bat in defense.
Works it in the gap on the leg side and picks up a single towards mid-wicket.
Back of a length ball on off, blocked back from the crease.
FOUR! Outside off, on a length, Sharma slashes hard and gets a thick outside edge which flies past the slip cordon and beats third man!
Full and outside off, swinging in, driven sweetly but straight to cover.
Full and on the pads, clipped through mid-wicket for an easy couple.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads. One run added to the total.
SIX! Massive hit! A length ball outside off, Rohit comes down the track and sends it sailing over the covers!
Full on middle, pushed towards mid on.
Full and outside off, Rohit looks to push but misses. That stayed low as well.
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot. They pick up a single.
Down the leg side, Rahul misses his flick and is hit on the pads. A leg bye taken.

DROPPED! Goodness me, Bangladesh have given a life to Rohit Sharma! Back of a length ball on off, Sharma sits back to pull and plays it aerially down to deep mid-wicket. Tamim, present there, puts down a dolly. A single taken.
Full and outside off, driven a tad uppishly but lands well short of cover.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Full and outside off, driven towards cover.
Outside off, coming back in, Rahul looks to tuck it to the leg side but gets a thick inside edge onto his pads. Saifuddin appeals for LBW but the umpire is not interested.

FOUR! Misfield from Shakib and Saifuddin is not happy. Full and on middle, Rahul flicks it through mid-wicket. Shakib Al Hasan gives it a good chase from deep mid-wicket, dives to his left but goes over the ball.
Full and outside off, punched straight to cover.
A length ball again, outside off, this time KL walks down the track and pushes it down the ground.
That stayed low! Outside off, on a length, Rahul looked to defend but the ball stayed low and beat the outside edge.
Full and outside off, Rahul watchfully takes his bat away.
Outside off, Rahul watchfully plays it behind point for a run.
A fractionally short ball, around middle, Rohit looks to help it fine but the extra bounce surprises him. It goes uppishly but lands wide of short fine leg. A single taken.
A length ball just around off, pushed back to the bowler.
On a length outside off, angling away, Rohit lets it go.
Around off, solidly defended.
Outside off, played behind point for a single.
Full on middle, flicked through mid-wicket for a run.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Full and outside off, driven straight to mid off.
Outside off, left alone.
Around off, defended watchfully.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
On middle and leg, clipped through mid-wicket for a couple.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
SIX! There he goes! Rohit is away in style. Short and outside off, Sharma swivels on the back foot and pulls it magnificently over mid-wicket!
Back of a length ball on off, Rohit goes on the back foot and punches it to covers. No swing at all.
WIDE. Short and down the leg side, Rohit looks to pull but misses.
Full and on middle and leg, clipped through square leg for a single.
Around middle, pushed down the ground.

OUT! Bowled! Perfect yorker ocne again. Too good for the number 11 batsman. It is on middle and off, Mustafizur looks to put his bat down but he misses. 2 in 2 for Bumrah. He won't get a hat-trick though are Bangladesh are bowled out. INDIA WIN BY 28 RUNS AND QUALIFY FOR THE SEMI-FINALS.
OUT! Bowled! A fast and straight yorker on middle, Rubel looks to put the bat down but he is late and the stumps are disturbed.
On the pads, Saifuddin flicks it down the leg side and gets a single.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR SAIFUDDIN. Only his 2nd one in ODIs. Full on off, Saifuddin smashes it straight down the ground. Virat Kohli in the deep runs and dives to his left but cannot stop it. Good effort from the skipper though.
Slower ball on a length, Rubel pulls it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Full toss on off, Saifuddin flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Very full, almost a yorker, on middle, Hossain digs it out behind the stumps, to Dhoni.
Outside off, a swing and a miss.
Better ball. Very full on middle, MS plays it to long on for a single.
FOUR! 37 needed of 21 balls. Short on the body, Saifuddin pulls it towards the backward square leg fence for a boundary.
WIDE! Bouncer is over the head of Saifuddin. Wide signalled by the umpire.
Full toss on  middle, Rubel does not take the full toll of it but just hits it to long on for a single.
Swing and miss. Full outside off, Hossain swings his bat at it but misses.
Full on middle, Rubel looks to hit it on the off side but gets a thick inside edge. The ball rolls to the on side and he takes one.
On the pads, MS flicks it to the on side for a run.
In the air but safe. Full on off, Rubel lofts it over cover-point. Pant in the deep misjudges it and takes it on a bounce. Single taken.
FOUR! That is hit with venom. Good length ball on off, Rubel smashes it over the bowler's head for a boundary.
Low full toss on off, Saifuddin strokes it towards long off for a single.
Dipping full toss on off, Saifuddin guides it to short third man.
On the pads, Saifuddin flicks it to the on side for a single.
FOUR! Extremely well played this. Saifuddin won't die without trying. Full on off, Saifuddin creams it wide of long off for a boundary.
WIDE! Bowls it down the leg side, Saifuddin looks to flick but misses. Wide signalled.
Full on off, Hossain looks to heave it on the off side, he gets a top edge which falls in no man's land for a single.
Full toss on the pads, Rubel flicks it to the man at mid-wicket.

OUT! Caught! Mortaza's cameo comes to an end. Slower ball outside off, Mortaza swings his bat at it. The ball takes the outside edge and flies to the right of Dhoni. He moves swiftly to that side and takes a relatively easy catch.

IN THE AIR....SIX! Slower ball on middle, Mortaza swings his bat at it. He does not time it well. It looks like Rahul at long on will have a chance. He stretches to his left but cannot keep it inside and it goes over the ropes for a six.
On the pads, Saifuddin flicks it wide of mid-wicket and gets a couple. 64 needed off the last 6 overs.
WIDE! In  a rare occurance, Bumrah misses his line and bowls it on the wrong side of the tramline. Wided by the umpire.
Slower ball. It is full on middle, Mortaza plays it towards square leg and gets to the other end.
Works it down the leg side for a single.
On the pads, Mortaza flicks it to the on side and takes a single.
Yorker on off. It is another brilliant one. Mortaza does well to get his bat down in time.

OUT! Bowled! Bumrah strikes in the very first ball of his come back over. Slower one bowled at 118 kph. Sabbir did not pick it at all. He swings his bat at it but misses. The ball goes onto hit the leg pole. This might be the final nail in the coffin in this chase, Bumrah has probably crashed all hopes Bangladesh had.
On middle and leg, Rahman flicks it towards mid-wicket and keeps the strike.
Another brilliantly bowled slower one. Rahman looks to run it down to third man but misses.
Off cutter on off, Sabbir guides it towards short third man and gets a single.
WIDE! Once again misses his line with a slower one and bowsl it on the wrong side of the tramline.
Excellent ball this. A perfect yorker on middle, Sabbir does really well to dig it out.
WIDE! Bowls it well outside off. It has been wided. Is pressure getting to the Indian bowlers?
Full toss around off, Saifuddin milks it to long on and gets a single.
Full on off, Sabbir lofts it over covers and to sweeper cover for one.
Back of a length, Sabbir looks to pull but it goes off the  inside edge of his bat to the on side and gets a single. 75 needed off 42.
Short again, this time Saifuddin pulls it to deep mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
FOUR! Shami is bowling the wrong lengths here. It is outside off, Saifuddin pulls it through square leg for a boundary.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Saifuddin taps it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Up and over! Overpitched on off, Saifuddin lofts it over mid off for a boundary. These two are slowly and steadily taking Bangladesh close here.
Good length ball on off and middle, Sabbir nudges it towards mid-wicket and gets a single.
Floated on off, Rahman strokes it to long off and takes one. 50-run stand comes between the two with that single.
On the pads, Saifuddin flicks it to the on side and gets a run.
Floated on off, Sabbir pushes it cover and gets a single.
This one keeps very low. Short outside off, turning away from the batter. Sabbir looks to cut but misses as the ball keeps really low. Rahman falls down after he swings his bat.
Shorter on off, Sabbir punches it to the man at cover.
WIDE! Chahal misses his line and bowls it down the leg side. It has been wided.
Tossed up outside off, Rahman looks to sweep but misses.
Outside off, left alone by Saifuddin.
Smart bowling this. Pandya sees Saifuddin come down the track so he bowls it slow on his pad. Saifuddin looks to hit but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Outside off and slower, Saifuddin swings his bat at it but misses.
On the pads, Rahman flicks it to the on side and gets a single.
Follows it up with a quick single. Good length ball on off, Saifuddin defends with soft hands to the off side and takes a quick run.
FOUR! Good start to the over this. 8 runs off the last two balls. Short on off, Saifuddin pulls it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR! Good end to the over for Bangladesh. Floated on middle, Sabbir sweeps it through square leg for a boundary. 96 runs more needed.
Shorter on off, Saifuddin punches it off his back foot to the off side for a single.
Darted on the pads, Saifuddin looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
The batsman has played it towards mid-wicket.
WIDE! Chahal misses his line and bowls it down the leg side. Wide signalled.
FOUR! Floated on the pads, Saifuddin looks to sweep but gets a top edge. It falls behind Bumrah at short fine leg. The ball bounces and races away from him for a boundary.
Flighted around off, Sabbir strokes it to sweeper cover for one.
FOUR! Shami has been taken to the cleaners here. Full on off, Saifuddin heaves it over mid-wicket. The ball bounces before the ropes and goes away for a boundary. 17 runs off the over.
Short ball on the pads, Saifuddin ducks under it.
FOUR! Power, brute power. Back of a length ball on off, Saifuddin smacks it over the mid on fence for a boundary.
Length ball on off, SR guides it down to third man for a single. 200 comes up for Bangladesh with that.
FOUR! Poor ball this. It is short and on the body, Sabbir pulls it fine down the leg side for a boundary.
FOUR! Sabbir comes down the track. Shami serves it short, Sabbir still manages to pull it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Floated on middle, Saifuddin blocks it.
On the pads, Saifuddin flicks it but finds the man at mid-wicket.
On the leg side, Saifuddin looks to flick but the ball kisses his thigh pad and goes to Dhoni.
Tossed up on the stumps, Saifuddin defends it off the back foot.
On the pads, Saifuddin flicks it to the man at short fine leg.
Floated on off, Rahman strokes it through covers for a single.
Slower bouncer, Saifuddin ducks under it. 125 needed off 84 balls.
Once again it short, Sabbir pulls it to the on side and takes one.
Good length ball on off, Rahman defends it off the front foot.
Back of a length ball on off, Rahman pulls it wide of deep square leg and gets a couple.
Good length ball outside off, Sabbir defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Short on off, Sabbir pulls it wide of square leg. Bumrah runs to his left and initially stops the ball with a dive but he cannot stop it from going to the fence.
WIDE! Bouncer goes over Sabbir's head. Wide signalled.
Around off, Rahman punches it to sweeper cover for a single.

Oh! Almost another chop on here. Good length ball outside off, Sabbir looks to run it down but gets a thick inside edge. Luckily it goes past the stumps and to the left of Dhoni. MS dives to his left and saves a certain boundary.
Very full on middle and off, Saifuddin flicks it to the on side and gets a single.
Full on middle, Sabbir strokes it wide of mid on and gets a single.
Slower one outside off, Sabbir swings his bat at it but misses.
On the pads, Sabbir flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on off, Saifuddin gets a leading edge towards point.

OUT! Caught! Is that the end of this chase for Bangladesh? Shakib makes room as Pandya runs in. Pandya follows him with his slower one. Shakib is early in his drive and ends up chipping it straight to Dinesh Karthik at cover. Body blow this for Bangladesh. One might feel India have served the knockout blow here. Shakib's lone fight comes to an end.
Cross-seam bouncer. Shakib looks to pull but misses.
On the pads, Sabbir whips it to fine leg for a single.
Slower one on off, Sabbir defends it off the front foot.
Good length ball on off, Shakib runs it down to third man for one.
Back of a length ball on off, Rahman looks to defend but it lobs off the upper half of his bat. Luckily it falls in no man's land.
Good length ball on off, Rahman defends it to cover.
Yorker on middle, Sabbir does well to get his bat down in time. Tough ball for a new batsman.
FOUR! Sabbir is off the mark with a boundary. Short ball on off, Rahman guides it down the third man fence for a boundary.

OUT! Another chop on! Bumrah gets his first. Slower one, bowled at 119 kph. Mosaddek was struggling to pick the slower ones and this time he is completely outdone by it. He looks to run it down but gets a thick inside edge onto the stumps. Bangladesh struggling here in this chase. They need someone to support Shakib Al Hasan.
On the pads, Shakib flicks it to the on side and gets a single.
Once again an off cutter. Mosaddek looks to flat bat but it goes to Dhoni behind the stumps off the bottom edge.
Slower one outside off, Shakib drags it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball on off, Shakib cuts it to point.
Slower ball. Mosaddek is outfoxed by it and ends up chipping it over covers. The ball lands in no man's land and they get a single.
On the pads, Shakib turns it on the on side and gets a single.
Short ball on off, Shakib looks to heave but it goes back to the bowler off the inner half of his bat.
Yorker on off, Mosaddek digs it out.
Length ball around off, Shakib guides it down to thid man and takes a single.
Yorker around off, Shakib does well to get his bat down in time.
FOUR! Off the edge! Short and wide outside off, Shakib looks to cut but it goes off the outside edge for a boundary down the third man fence.
Length ball on off, Mosaddek guides it down to third man and gets a single.
Good length ball on off, Hossain cuts it but finds point.
Good length ball on off, Shakib punches it to mid off.
Mosaddek gets off the mark with a single down to third man.

OUT! Another budding stand is broken. Hardik bangs it in short. It comes quicker than Liton expected. Also it is at an uncomfortable height, Das still goes for the pull but it comes off the upper half of his bat. It lobs up and goes to the left of mid-wicket. Dinesh Karthik takes a simple catch. Second wicket in the game for Pandya. He did not have a good day with the bat but he is proving his worth with the bat.
On the pads, Liton flicks it to the man at mid-wicket.
SIX! That's hammered away. Full on middle, Liton smashes it over the long on fence for a maximum. That was a meaty blow by Das.
Good length ball on  middle and leg. It goes with the angle, Liton looks to flick but misses. The ball hits him on his pads. There is a stifled appeal but it is turned down.
Slower bouncer, Shakib pulls it over mid-wicket but does not time it well. Still manages to get a couple.
Short around off, Shakib pulls it over mid-wicket for a couple.
On the pads, flicked to the on side for a run.
Punched to the off side for a single.

On the pads, Shakib flicks it towards square leg. Shakib runs the first one hard and goes for the second. Hardik  gets to the ball and sends a good throw at the keeper's end. Virat Kohli dislodges the bails as Shakib puts in a dive. He looks confident. The umpire takes it upstairs and replays show Shakib's dive saved him.
The batsman has played it towards mid-wicket. They pick up a single.

50 for Shakib. His 46th in ODIs. Once again it is a big game and the big man has delivered. Length ball on off, Shakib punches it through point and gets a couple to bring up his 50. Shakib knows the job is not done here as he holds the key in this chase.

FOUR! Moves to 48. Good length ball around off, Shakib punches it through covers and scores a magnificent boundary. The fielder at short cover gets it on a bad bounce which makes it difficult for him to stop.
Good length ball on off, Das punches it wide of mid on and gets a single.

Shorter on off, Shakib pulls it wide of mid-wicket and takes one. Liton wants the second and he comes out for it. Shakib though sends him back. The fielder sends a good throw at the keeper's end. Liton puts in a dive which saves him as Dhoni takes the bails off. The square leg umpire still takes it upstairs. The TV umpire has one look and signals Not Out on the giant screen.
The batsman has driven it straight down the ground.
On the pads, Shakib looks to flick but gets hit on the pads.
Outside off, Das looks to drive but misses.
This time cuts it through point and gets a couple.
Around off, Das strokes it to the man at point.

Good length ball on off, Das punches it to mid off and gets a single. The fielder there has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. The ball goes behind and Shami fails to collect the ball in the first attempt allowing them to take the second.
Length ball on off, Das plays it to point. The fielder there dives to his right and saves runs.
Outside off, Das cuts it wide of sweeper cover for a couple.
Good length ball on off, LD plays it down to third man for a single to keep the strike.
Great shot but fantastic fielding from KL Rahul!  Short ball on the body, Liton plays a wonderful pull towards backward square leg. Rahul runs to his right and puts a dive to save a certain boundary.
Full around off, Das drives it to mid on off the inner half of his bat.
On the pads, Shakib looks to flick but the ball rolls off his thigh pad towards the fine leg region and they take a leg bye.
Length ball on off, Das pushes it to sweeper cover for a single.
Good length ball on middle and off, Shakib turns it to the leg side and gets a single.
Tossed up on middle, Shakib milks it to long on and gets a single.
On the pads, Shakib flicks it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on the pads, Shakib comes down the track and taps it back towards the bowler off the lower half of his bat.
Flighted on off, Das sweeps it to square leg for a single.
Floated on off, Liton defends it to point.
Leg spinner outside off, Liton strokes it to point.
Fuller on off, Liton drives it towards point for single.
Around off, Shakib taps it to third man and rotates the strike.
Length ball on off, Das gets off the mark with a guide down to third man.
Another short ball, Liton sways away from it.
Bouncer! It is outside off, Liton throws his bat at it but misses. He looks at the square leg umpire but no signal from him.
On the pads, Shakib turns it to fine leg and gets a single.

OUT! Caught! Straight to the man! Chahal finally strikes in Edgbaston. Tossed up outside off, Rahim gets down and looks to sweep. He connects well but finds Shami who is standing somewhere between square leg and mid-wicket. This could be a massive blow to Bangladesh. 194 more needed from 162 balls.
Outside off, Mushfiqur looks to run it down to third man but ends up chopping it on the bounce towards backward point. He is halfway down the track for the single but is sent back.
FOUR! Very well played. Right in the gap. Short and outside off, a bit slow in the air. Rahim goes back and cuts it between short third man and backward point.
Landed outside off, spinning away, watchfully left alone.
On middle, pushed through mid on for a single.
On middle and off, Shakib looks to flick but the ball spins away and takes the leading edge. Does not carry to point.
Full on middle, Shakib glances on the leg side and keeps the strike with a single.
Short ball on off, Rahim pulls it over square leg for a single.
On the pads, Shakib flicks it to the on side and rotates the strike.
On off, Rahim pushes it towards cover and takes one.
Good length ball on off, Shakib guides it down to third man and follows the four with a single.
FOUR! Cut and cut sharp. Good length ball outside off, Shakib cuts it hard through point for a boundary. He is one off the best players on the off side.
Comes down the track and  strokes it to long on to keep the strike.
Punched off the back foot by the batsman. One run added to the total.
Tossed up on middle, Shakib milks it to long on for an easy run.
Once again it is on the pads, Shakib flicks but finds short fine leg.
On the pads, Shakib flicks it to the man at mid-wicket.
Ohh! Tossed up on  middle, Shakib comes down the track and looks to flick, the ball though gets an inside edge and luckily hits Shakib's pad.
The batsman plays the square cut. The batsmen have run through for a single.
Short ball, Rahim pulls it to fine leg and gets a single.
On a length, Shakib taps it to third man and rotates the strike.
Short ball on off, Shakib cuts it wide of deep point and gets a couple.
Fuller on off, Shakib pushes it to cover.
Good length ball on off, Mushfiqur taps it towards third man and looks for two. Unfortunately though Rahim slips at the bowler's end so has to be satisfied with a single.
Floated on off, Rahim defends it with soft hands and gets a single. 19 runs have come off the last 2 overs.
FOUR! Two in two! Tossed up on middle and off, Rahim gets down on one knee and slog sweeps it over mid-wicket. No one in the deep there. The ball bounces a couple of times and goes to the fence.
FOUR! Poor ball! Leg spinner on the pads, Rahim just guides it fine down the leg side. The ball beats Hardik Pandya at short fine leg who dives to his right and goes onto the fence.
On the pads, Shakib turns it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Flighted on off, Shakib comes down the track and flicks it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on middle, Shakib strokes it to the man at mid-wicket.
Back of a length ball on off, Shakib pulls it towards fine leg and keeps the strike. 9 runs off the over.
FOUR! Edgy one! Off cutter around off, Shakib looks to drive but it goes very fine past the keeper off the outside edge of his bat for a boundary.
Once again short, Rahim pulls it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Back of a length ball around off, Mushfiqur pulls it wide of deep mid-wicket and gets a couple. Shakib wanted the third but Mushfiqur says no.
Length ball on off, Mushfiqur defends it off the front foot to point.
Length ball on off, Shakib guides it down to third man and gets a single.
Driven towards the mid off region.
On the pads, this time Shakib flicks it wide of short mid-wicket and gets a single.
On the pads, Shakib flicks it to the man at short mid-wicket.
Tosssed up on off, Mushfiqur strokes it towards cover and gets a single.
Chahal getting good amount of spin here. It is pitched on middle but goes towards Shakib's pad. He flicks it fine down the leg side and gets a single.
Floated on off, Rahim strokes it to long off for a single.
Mushfiqur is off the mark. Good length ball on off, Rahim guides it down to third man and gets a single. Successful start for Hardik. 2 runs and a wicket for HP to begin with.
Short ball again. It is on the leg side, Mushfiqur goes for the hook but misses. Not been wided.
Bouncer! Rahim gets on his toes and keeps it down.
Good length ball on off, Rahim defends it off the front foot.
Back of a length ball on off, Rahim blocks it off the back foot.

OUT! Caught! Hardik strikes in his very first over. He bowls a length ball outside off. It is a slower one. Soumya punches it but cannot keep it down. The ball goes straight to Kohli at short cover. The Indian skipper is ecstatic as it was Sarkar's lbw appeal that made them lose their review. Crucial wicket this as Sarkar was starting to look dangerous. Bangladesh need to convert their starts here.
WIDE! False start for Pandya as his bouncer goes over Sarkar's head.
The batsman works it down the leg side. One run added to the total.
Floated on middle, Shakib strokes it to long on for one.
Flighted on off, Shakib sweeps it towards mid-wicket.
Floated on off, Sarkar looks to defend but it goes to the on side off the inner half of his bat. Sarkar takes a run.
Shorter on off and middle, Shakib milks it down to long on and gets a single.
Shorter on the pads, Shakib looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
FOUR! Poor from Shami! Good length ball outside off, Soumya cuts it over cover and gets a boundary. Sweeper cover gives it a chase but comes second best.
On the pads, Shakib flicks it to the on side and rotates the strike.
Bouncer! Shakib sits under it and lets it go to the keeper.
Full on off, Shakib drives it straight to mid off.
Now guides the next ball down to third man and gets a single.
FOUR! The mid off is up so this shot has a very minimal risk. Fuller around off, Sarkar lofts it over mid off. He does not time it well but has timed well enough to get a boundary.
Once again finds short mid-wicket with his glance. 6 runs off Chahal's first.
On the pads, Shakib flicks it to the man at short mid-wicket.
Leg spinner on the pads, Shakib flicks it towards fine leg and gets a couple.
Floated on the stumps, Shakib blocks it.
Short on off and middle, Shakib punches it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Not the start Chahal would have wanted. Floated on the pads, Shakib paddles it fine down the leg side for a boundary.
Length ball around off, Shakib runs it down to third man for a single.
Played to the point region by Shakib.
Play and a miss. Good length ball outside off, Shakib looks to run it down to third man but misses.
Back of a length ball on off, Sarkar taps it to the off side and gets a single.

NOT OUT! India have lost their sole review. Good length ball pitching on middle, it nips back in sharply. Sarkar looks to defend but the ball hits him on his pad. The Indian players put a big appeal but it is turned down. Kohli has a chat with Shami and then decides to take it upstairs. Ultra Edge rolls in and it is a touch and go decision as the ball seems to have hit the bat and pad at a very similar time. The TV umpire does not have a conclusive view so the decision stays as the on field umpire's. Kohli is not happy and argues with the umpires. Got to feel for him. He is asking why hasn't the Ball Tracker been loaded. Because if it is umpire's call, then India would not lose their review. However, because the third umpire is not sure whether the ball hit the bat or not, he did not check the Ball Tracker. It is showed now and the ball is clipping the leg stump. The decision would have stayed not out but at least India would not have lost their review...
FOUR! Crisp! Full on off, Sarkar drives it with authority through covers for a boundary.
Length ball on middle and leg, Shakib looks to defend but the ball nips back in and hits him on the thigh pad.
WIDE! Bouncer goes over Shakib's head and it has been wided.
Fuller on off, Sarkar lofts it over covers but there is a man in the deep there so just a single.
Once again on the pads, Shakib turns it behind square on the leg side for a single.
On the pads, Shakib flicks it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! That's the shot of a man in form. Full on middle and leg, Shakib delightfully drives it through mid on to get his first boundary of this game.
Full ball on the stumps, Shakib pushes it to mid off.
Once again stroked to the man at point. End of Powerplay 1. Bangladesh are 40/1, India were 69/0.
Good length ball on off, Sarkar plays it to the man at point.
Shakib is off the mark. On the pads, Shakib flicks it to the on side and takes a single.

OUT! Chopped on! India's strike bowler this World Cup has given them the breakthrough. Good length ball just outside off, Tamim looks to run it down to third man but it comes off the toe end of his bat. The ball then goes onto disturb the stumps. Tamim fails to convert his start here. India have broken the opening stand.
Good length ball on off, Sarkar works it through mid-wicket for a single.
On top of middle, Sarkar pushes it to mid on and takes one.
On top of middle, Sarkar pushes it to mid on and takes one.
On the pads, Tamim turns it towards fine leg for a run.
On the pads, Soumya flicks it to the on side and gets a single.
Comes around the wicket for Sarkar. He defends it off the front foot.
Cramps him for room and bowls it on the pads, Tamim tucks it towards mid-wicket and gets a single.
Play and a miss. Good length ball outside off, Tamim goes for a big drive but misses.
Good length ball on off, Soumya taps it to point. 6 off Shami's first.
Follows it up with a solid defense.
FOUR! Up and over! Full outside off, Sarkar slices it over cover-point. The fielder at third man is at 45 so he cannot stop it. First boundary for Sarkar and this should give him a lot of confidence.
Good length ball close to the body, Sarkar guides it wide of third man and gets a brace.
Another one that comes in with the angle. It is on middle, Soumya taps it to point off the upper half of his bat.
Steams in from round the wicket and bowls it on the pads, Soumya tucks it towards mid-wicket.
On top of the stumps, Tamim defends it off the front foot to see through the over.

Mistimed but safe. Short ball, just away from Tamim. He looks to pull but does not time it. It is timed well enough to go over short mid-wicket. Pant mops it up, the batsmen meanwhile come back for the second.
On the pads once again, Tamim flicks it to mid-wicket.
On the pads, Tamim flicks it towards square leg. Shami cleans it up from fine leg but they get a couple.
Bouncer. It is on the body, Tamim sits under it. The ploy here is clear, they are looking to bowl it closer to Tamim's body.
On middle and leg, Tamim flicks it to the man at short mid-wicket.
Good length ball on off, Sarkar taps it to point.

BOUNCER! It is quick and close to the body, Tamim ducks under it. The ball keeps rising but Dhoni does well to jump and gets his outstretched right hand to partially stop it. The ball goes behind him allowing them to take a bye.
Fuller on middle, Tamim pushes it to mid on.
Good length ball on off, Tamim looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto his pads.

FOUR OVERTHROWS! Back of a length ball on off, Sarkar taps it towards backward point and calls for a quick run. Tamim responds, Hardik gets to the ball quickly and has a shy at the keeper's end. He misses. The backup behind is too close and it goes past him to the fence.
Good length ball on off, Sarkar drives it to point.
Comes 'round the wicket to Soumya and bowls it short. Sarkar taps it towards backward point off the upper half of his bat and takes a single.
A run after 10 dots. Fuller on off, Iqbal pushes it towards mid off and takes a quick single.
10 dot ball on the trot here. It is on middle and leg, Tamim flicks it but finds short mid-wicket.
Another one hit on the legs here. Bhuvneshwar has corrected his line to Tamim here. It is on the pads, Iqbal once again misses his flick.
Once again cramping Tamim for room. Bowls it on middle and leg, Iqbal looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Good length ball on the pads, Tamim looks to flick but misses. There are oohs and aahs from the Indian players but the pitching looked to be just outside leg.
Maiden. Good length ball on top of the stumps. Soumya defends it towards mid off to see through the over.
Play and a miss. Good length ball outside off. It is in the line to force a drive. Sarkar goes for it but misses. 5 dots on the trot here in this over.
Good length ball on off, Soumya defends it off the front foot towards mid off.
This one comes in with the angle. It is on middle, Sarkar defends it off the front foot.
Beauty! Good length ball pitching on off. It moves away after hitting the deck. Sarkar looks to defend but gets beaten by the away movement. Such a delightful ball to watch.
Fuller on off, Soumya pushes it to the man at mid off.
Now flicks it wide of deep mid-wicket and gets a couple. 7 off this Bhuvi over.
FOUR! Once again a gorgeous cut by Tamim. Bhuvneshwar bowls it on a length outside off, Tamim cuts it with ease through point for his 3rd boundary of the game.
This time he is able to guide it down to third man and gets a single.
Length ball around off, Sarkar looks to play it down towards third man but ends up chopping it to the man at second slip.
Good length ball on off, Sarkar pushes it to mid off.
Good length ball on middle, Sarkar defends it off the front foot.

FOUR! Comes 'round the wicket and serves it on a length outside off. Bumrah, on this occasion is guilty of giving Tamim width to play with. Tamim accepts the invitation and cuts it through point for a boundary. Expensive start for Bumrah. 8 runs off his first.
Corrects his line and bowls it on off, Tamim blocks it.
FOUR! First one of the innings! It is full on the pads, Tamim plays a gorgeous flick shot through mid-wicket to get the first boundary.
Hits the deck hard on a length, Tamim confidently defends it.
Good length ball on off, Tamim defends it off the front foot.
Fuller on middle, Tamim pushes it to mid on.

Beauty to finish. This one comes in and comes in a lot. It is pitched on off, Sarkar looks to play it but it comes in so much that it hits him on his pad. Tidy start. Just a run off the first over. Tamim looks to be in the mood in his 200th ODI.
Way outside off. This is the one which goes away from the left-hander. It is just inside the tramline. Soumya initially looks to play at it but misses.
The chase is off the mark. Full outside off, Tamim looks to drive but it goes off the outer half of his bat towards third man for a single.
Flash and miss. It is on the fifth stump line, Tamim throws his bat at it but does not connect.
Now bowls it closer to the body, Tamim tucks it to the man at mid-wicket.
Bhuvneshwar starts with a length ball outside off, Tamim does not go after it and lets it carry to the keeper.
